name: New Walke Food Station

reviews.review_text: I had order veg fried rice, manchow soup and dal khichdi for my baby..the soup was spilled. A layer of oil was floating on the khichdi nd taste as usual bakkwaass

I've been here many times right from the time it was started , during that time it was one of the best pure veg restaurants around there but now recently their services  and ambience have gone down to quite a noticeable extend also the prices have increased and quantity has decreased and the staff also seems to be lacking the enthusiasm to work!

Went here recently glad to see come positive changes. Still a lot to improve upon but it’s getting one more extra star from me.

The waiter in the AC room is very unprofessional, lazy to take orders, we ordered cheesy fries and he is like it will take 20 minutes. The owner has to look into it I have observed him 3-4 times.
Before even finishing the food the waiter kept the bill on the table that looked like he was not even interested in the work and didn't want to take any other order.

description:
**New Walke Food Station: A Dive into Mapusa's Vegetarian Haven**

Nestled in the bustling heart of Mapusa, New Walke Food Station welcomes diners with a composite rating of 3.5 out of 5, earned from over 1300 reviews. This vegetarian eatery garners attention for its popular offerings, particularly the snacks (30 mentions), pav bhaji (26 mentions), and samosas (18 mentions), while being frequently highlighted for its hygiene standard (20 mentions). However, customer sentiment is mixed, as evident from their feedback.

**Ambiance & Design**

The restaurant features a blend of simplicity and vibrancy that reflects a casual dining ethos. Photographs reveal a brightly lit interior with a modest yet welcoming design. Views of the dining area show clean surfaces and functional furnishings that promote a laid-back atmosphere, ideal for families and friends. While there were mentions of decreased enthusiasm in service and a decline in ambiance quality over time, a few patrons noted positive changes during recent visits, suggesting that New Walke Food Station might be on the path to rejuvenation.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

Famed for its array of vegetarian delights, the menu boasts favorites like pav bhaji—a dish that continues to attract loyal customers. However, the mixed reviews on dishes like the vegetable fried rice and dal khichdi indicate inconsistency in culinary execution. One review described the khichdi as overly oily and lacking flavor, while another commenter appreciated a return to positive changes, hinting that the kitchen might be recalibrating its offerings. The presentation is straightforward yet effective, as seen in the vivid photos showcasing the food, though it appears that not all dishes have wowed every palate.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Diners have expressed concerns over service efficiency and staff professionalism. Several reviews pointed out a decline in attentiveness, with reports of long waits for orders and waitstaff seemingly disengaged. For instance, one reviewer shared a frustrating experience where the waiter preemptively placed the bill on the table despite unfinished meals. While some patrons noticed this lack of enthusiasm from the staff, others appreciated the improvements noted during their latest visits. It appears the management has recognized the need for an upgrade in service standards, which could boost overall dining satisfaction.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Social media commentary aligns with the sentiment observed in the reviews, indicating that while New Walke Food Station enjoyed popularity in its early days as a pioneering vegetarian restaurant, maintaining that status has proved challenging with fluctuating service quality and menu consistency. While not currently leading in accolades, this eatery remains a topic of local conversation, suggesting room for growth and improvement.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The provided images complement the narrative well, showcasing the restaurant's ambiance and some food items. One photo captures a vibrant dish that hints at the restaurant's focus on color and freshness, while the others portray the casual dining layout. However, it is important to note that customer experiences highlighted in the reviews suggest a need for a greater attention to detail in food preparation and service.

In conclusion, while New Walke Food Station offers a nostalgic destination for many Mapusa locals craving vegetarian snacks, it faces a challenge in maintaining reliable quality and service. With a little extra care in both kitchen output and staff engagement, this restaurant has the potential to reclaim its former status as a beloved local eatery.
